<figureCitation box="[159,259,1658,1683]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 22" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,197,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 22. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 1 – 2. A. alstonii. 3 – 4. A. nurtia ludibunda. 5 – 6. A. pulchra. 7 – 8. A. bonita. 9 – 10. A. amalfreda. 11 – 12. A. physis phyton. 13 – 14. A. halli sp. nov. holotype. 15 – 16. A. celata. 17 – 20. A. gallardi sp. nov. 17 – 18. Male holotype. 19 – 20. Female (tentative determination). 21 – 22. A. aparamilla. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233289/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">
Figs 
<number box="[215,259,1659,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="1.73" valueMax="2.46" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,300,1658,1683]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">46</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1730,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">
In 
<number box="[181,236,1731,1755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a single male was collected at the hilltop while resting on the underside of a leaf about seven meters above the ground, around 
<number box="[372,400,1766,1791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="18.0">18</number>
:00h. In 
<number box="[495,551,1767,1791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="2014.0">2014</number>
three males were collected in a same day resting on the underside of leaves in the same tree from the record of 
<number box="[517,572,1803,1827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="2011.0">2011</number>
around 
<number box="[664,693,1802,1827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="16.0">16</number>
:00h.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1730,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">
This rare species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[618,713,1838,1863]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smart" box="[727,859,1839,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" refString="Smart, P. (1979) A new species of Argyrogramma (Lepidoptera: Nemeobiidae) from Trinidad. Aurelian, 1, 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="1979">
Smart 
<number box="[802,859,1839,1863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and further recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1137,1302,1838,1863]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard 
<number box="[283,343,1874,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The Brazilian specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[707,828,1874,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alstonii">
<emphasis box="[707,828,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">A. alstonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a dark orange color, like the 
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1436,1874,1899]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
specimens; however, the light blue spot on the upperside of the forewing is larger than the 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1324,1910,1935]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[158,462,1946,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard 
<number box="[405,462,1946,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and the 
<typeStatus box="[566,668,1946,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="228">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
